21
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:36,040
{\pos(320,220)}曼克

22
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,700
{\an8}维克托维尔  37公里

23
00:01:55,580 --> 00:02:00,450
{\an8}北弗迪农场

24
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:15,160
{\an7}{\pos(78.192,136.158)}外景  维克托维尔  度假农场  白天  1940年

25
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:27,310
没关系  我自己能走  不用帮忙
It's all right. I've got this. I'm good.

26
00:02:36,610 --> 00:02:37,500
来
Here.

27
00:02:46,690 --> 00:02:48,360
我叫人把东西安置到了客厅
I had them set you up out here

28
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,670
这样你就不会太受限制
so you wouldn't feel quite so confined.

29
00:02:50,810 --> 00:02:53,450
女士们住两间卧室
The ladies will scandalize the neighborhood

30
00:02:53,450 --> 00:02:55,520
这想必会震惊街坊邻里
by occupying both bedrooms.

31
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:58,660
我会住在镇上一家田园风情的水疗店
I will be staying in town at a bucolic spa called,

32
00:02:58,660 --> 00:03:01,650
说出来你可能不信  名叫"从军记水疗店"
if you can believe it, the Shoulder Arms.

33
00:02:58,660 --> 00:03:01,650
{\an3}{\pos(380,235)}与查理·卓别林的电影《从军记》同名

34
00:03:01,650 --> 00:03:03,280
我会在那里改稿
I will do my editing there.

35
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,050
你也知道
As you know,

36
00:03:04,050 --> 00:03:06,860
芙蕾达小姐不仅是护士  她还是理疗师
Fraulein Freda is not only a nurse and physical therapist,

37
00:03:06,870 --> 00:03:09,210
在她的祖国学的是营养学
she studied nutrition back in the old country.

38
00:03:09,210 --> 00:03:12,370
-是吗  亲爱的小姐  -是的  豪斯曼先生
- Ja, liebes Fräulein? - Jawohl, Herr Houseman.

39
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:15,170
这里禁酒
It's a dry house.

40
00:03:15,180 --> 00:03:17,880
农场主人不允许住客喝酒
The owner of the ranch doesn't permit alcohol.

41
00:03:18,420 --> 00:03:19,840
但你是宾州人
But you're from Pennsylvania.

42
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:21,120
一定习惯了
You're no doubt used to it.

43
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,510
救场的来了
Saved by the proverbial bell.

44
00:03:24,810 --> 00:03:26,550
麻烦放在这里
Set it here, please.

45
00:03:27,220 --> 00:03:29,220
小心  小心
And, uh, careful. Careful.

46
00:03:30,090 --> 00:03:30,870
谢谢
Thank you.

47
00:03:35,970 --> 00:03:37,030
看好了
Observe.

48
00:03:39,710 --> 00:03:41,840
你一定会拼尽全力下床拿到它
Naturally, you'll do your damnedest to get at it.

49
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,510
等你完成初稿
By the time you finish the first draft,

50
00:03:43,510 --> 00:03:45,090
也就是90天后  依这个运动量
which is to say, in 90 days,

51
00:03:45,090 --> 00:03:47,780
你应该都能成为世界级的短跑健将了
you should be a world-class sprinter.

52
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:51,350
瑞塔  过来好吗
Rita, come in here, will you?

53
00:03:52,090 --> 00:03:53,820
这是亚历山大夫人
This is Mrs. Alexander.

54
00:03:53,820 --> 00:03:55,400
她一分钟能打100个词
She types 100 perfect words a minute

55
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,450
还能像先知一样记录口述
and takes dictation like a clairvoyant.

56
00:03:57,450 --> 00:03:59,840
瑞塔·亚历山大  赫尔曼·曼凯维奇
Rita Alexander, Herman Mankiewicz.

57
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,510
你好吗  曼凯维奇先生
How do you do, Mr. Mankiewicz?

58
00:04:01,860 --> 00:04:04,270
这得画个问号
That's a big question.

59
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:06,190
因为你喜欢在夜里创作
Well, since you like working nights,

60
00:04:06,190 --> 00:04:08,120
瑞塔过的是伦敦时间
Rita here runs on London time.

61
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:10,930
她丈夫是一名英国皇家空军的英勇飞行员
Her husband is one of our bold lads in the RAF.

62
00:04:10,930 --> 00:04:12,520
开的是...什么来着  瑞塔
Flies... What is it, Rita?

63
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,070
-喷火式战斗机吗  -飓风战斗机
- Spitfires? - Hurricanes.

64
00:04:14,070 --> 00:04:16,770
-值得同情  我为你祈祷  -你说什么
- My sympathy and prayers. - I beg your pardon?

65
00:04:16,770 --> 00:04:19,990
毕竟轴心国开的是BF109型战斗机
Given the speed, climb, and turning radius

66
00:04:19,990 --> 00:04:21,630
它的速度  爬升率和转弯半径...
of the Messerschmitt Bf 109...

67
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:24,160
但愿我们用不着你的同情  曼凯维奇先生
I hope we won't need your sympathy, Mr. Mankiewicz.

68
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:27,240
祷告与作战我们都能胜任
We'll do the praying and the fighting.

69
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:30,730
我每周会与奥森见面  汇报我们的进展
I will meet with Orson weekly. Keep him to date on our progress.

70
00:04:30,730 --> 00:04:32,760
我们的期望很高
We're expecting great things.

71
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:37,060
那个编剧是怎么说的  "讲述你了解的故事"
What is it the writer says? "Tell the story you know."

72
00:04:39,410 --> 00:04:41,770
我可不认识那个编剧
I don't know that writer.

73
00:04:44,870 --> 00:04:45,630
你好
Hello.

74
00:04:46,510 --> 00:04:48,760
是的  他就在这里
Yes. Yes, he's right here.

75
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:50,020
你要的东西应该都准备了
Well, you should have everything.

76
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:52,080
要是落了什么  你可以写在写字板上
If I've forgotten, there's a clipboard.

77
00:04:55,620 --> 00:04:57,430
-你好  -他们去叫他了
- Yes? Hello? - They're getting him.

78
00:04:58,150 --> 00:05:01,680
我们的神童确实有拿捏时机的天赋
Our wunderkind does have the gift of theatrical timing.

79
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:04,990
奥森  你好  我们刚到
Orson, hello. We just got in.

80
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:17,620
-你好  -曼克
- Hello. - Mank!

81
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:20,280
豪斯曼说你现在任我们差遣了
Houseman tells me we have you just where we want you.

82
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:21,630
我真走运
Lucky me.

83
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:24,920
-你的腿怎么样  -大腿骨和髋骨接上了
- How's the leg? - "Thigh bone's connected to the hip bone."

84
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:25,790
好极了
Excellent.

85
00:05:25,790 --> 00:05:28,060
准备好去猎杀大白鲸了吗
Ready and willing to hunt the great white whale?

86
00:05:25,790 --> 00:05:29,990
{\an3}{\pos(380,235)}出自名著《白鲸》

87
00:05:28,060 --> 00:05:29,990
你就叫我亚哈船长吧
Just call me Ahab.

88
00:05:30,210 --> 00:05:32,890
我听说我们有90天时间
I understand we've 90 days.

89
00:05:32,890 --> 00:05:34,850
改成60天吧
Let's aim for 60.

90
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,870
他刚砍了一个月时间
He's just cut a month.

91
00:05:36,890 --> 00:05:39,910
我以前在水星剧院五天就能给你写完
I used to do it in five for you at the Mercury.

92
00:05:39,910 --> 00:05:40,950
这也太悠闲了吧
This is leisurely.

93
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:44,910
-先定60天  到时候再商量  -最喜欢打商量了
- Sixty days, and then we can noodle. - Nothing like a good noodle.

94
00:05:45,180 --> 00:05:47,690
你砍掉30天时间
Is the reason you lopped 30 days

95
00:05:47,690 --> 00:05:50,010
是腾时间让雷电华的法务审批吗
to run it past the RKO legal?

96
00:05:50,010 --> 00:05:50,990
我不是和你说过了吗  曼克
I thought I told you, Mank.

97
00:05:50,990 --> 00:05:53,060
我有最终剪辑权  最终一切权
I have final cut, final everything.

98
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:54,610
没有制片厂从中插足
There are no studio notes.

99
00:05:54,610 --> 00:05:56,990
出了问题只能怪我们自己
We'll have no one but ourselves to blame.

100
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:59,530
-60天然后再商量  -威尔斯先生  准备好了
- Sixty days and a noodle. - Mr. Welles, we're ready.

101
00:05:59,530 --> 00:06:01,630
我得走了  要去给《黑暗的心》试镜
Gotta run. I'm doing tests for Heart of Darkness.

102
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:04,360
少来了  小约·康拉德
Oh, little that, lesser Joe Conrad.

103
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:04,360
{\an3}{\pos(380,235)}约瑟夫·康拉德是《黑暗的心》原著作者

104
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:06,680
如果有人问起  就说你在改编剧本
If anyone should ask, tell 'em you're adapting.

105
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:09,710
你不了解这个阳光普照的臭水沟  朋友
Oh, you don't know this sun-bleached sewer here, my friend.

106
00:06:09,710 --> 00:06:11,490
在好莱坞的中心放个屁
Break wind at Hollywood and Vine,

107
00:06:11,490 --> 00:06:14,430
圣莫尼卡的制片人就能闻到味儿
and a producer in Santa Monica reports a ruptured main.

108
00:06:14,430 --> 00:06:17,370
我确实不了解这地方  暂时还不了解
No, I don't know this burgh, not yet.

109
00:06:17,370 --> 00:06:19,150
我在精神上与你同在  曼克
I'm toiling with you in spirit, Mank.

110
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:21,210
怎么没听到打字声
And I don't hear any typing.

111
00:06:25,150 --> 00:06:26,510
没交待什么
No notes.

112
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:29,970
然后他就满了24岁
And then he turns 24.

113
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:33,450
身陷囹圄
Trapped.

114
00:06:36,290 --> 00:06:40,290
{\an7}{\pos(73.372,131.881)}内景  曼凯维奇家  夜晚  几周前

115
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:47,900
我帮你把衣服脱了
Let me take off these clothes.

116
00:06:49,210 --> 00:06:53,750
我刚达到完美的平衡  他们就让我走人了
They let me go just as I achieved perfect equilibrium.

117
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:57,170
我不愿意跟片场一半的制片人合作
I won't work with half the producers on the lot,

118
00:06:57,170 --> 00:06:59,950
而另一半不愿意跟我合作
and the other half won't work with me.

119
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:01,830
这是什么  赛马报道吗
What's this, a racing form?

120
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:04,850
不要看  不要学
You stop reading, you stop learning.

121
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:06,280
别动
Hold still.

122
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:09,560
躺好
Lay back.

123
00:07:11,990 --> 00:07:13,640
请给我点根烟
Cigarette, please.

124
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,960
赫米  你要是对着火柴哈口气
Hermie, if a match gets anywhere near your breath,

125
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:16,950
你身上都会起火
you'll burst into flames.

126
00:07:16,950 --> 00:07:19,720
连那条狗的名字都难听得要命
Even the dog's name is awful.

127
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:22,330
听着还以为是个日本男仆呢
Sounds like a Japanese houseboy.

128
00:07:22,330 --> 00:07:24,740
记住我说的  莎拉
You mark my words, Sara.

129
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:29,030
《绿野仙踪》会搞垮那家制片厂
The Wizard of Oz is gonna sink that studio.

130
00:07:29,030 --> 00:07:31,540
睡吧  你明天还要开车去纽约
Sleep. You're driving to New York tomorrow.

131
00:07:32,550 --> 00:07:36,640
还记得你以前从东部坐火车吗
Remember when you used to take the train from back East?

132
00:07:36,650 --> 00:07:38,910
我则会在阿尔伯克基偷偷溜上车
I'd sneak aboard in Albuquerque

133
00:07:38,910 --> 00:07:41,040
然后裸着身子爬进你的隔间
and climb into your compartment naked.

134
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:44,000
我还记得我在柏林度过蜜月
I also remember how I spent my honeymoon in Berlin,

135
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,130
妓女们整晚在楼梯间跑上跑下的
with hookers running up and down the stairs all night

136
00:07:46,130 --> 00:07:49,240
就因为我家那位潇洒的记者住不起好酒店
because my dashing correspondent couldn't afford a nice hotel.

137
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,420
那些日子真是美好啊
Weren't those the days?

138
00:07:50,420 --> 00:07:53,170
是啊  那些夜晚也不赖
Yeah, yeah, and the nights weren't bad either.

139
00:07:53,530 --> 00:07:56,180
-施努兹  -最后一次理你  怎么了
- Schnutz. - For the last time, what?

140
00:07:56,180 --> 00:07:59,170
-这是哪一年  -赫尔曼
- What year is it? - Herman...

141
00:07:59,170 --> 00:08:02,850
-我本该有所成就的  -赫米
- I should have done something by now. - Oh, Hermie...

142
00:08:02,850 --> 00:08:04,830
给我个指示吧  上帝
Give me a sign, oh, Lord.

143
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:09,830
我就像您的仆人摩西  不过我不会那么廉价
I am as your servant Moses, though I won't work half as cheap.

144
00:08:09,830 --> 00:08:12,020
快睡吧  小傻子
Go to sleep, meshuggener.

145
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,410
-施努兹  -又怎么了
- Schnutz? - What?

146
00:08:16,410 --> 00:08:18,420
你为什么这么迁就我
Why do you put up with me?

147
00:08:20,690 --> 00:08:21,930
我也不知道
I don't know.

148
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:24,570
前院的灌木
That bush in the front yard,

149
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:28,880
如果今晚着火了  你能告诉我一声吗
if it catches fire tonight, you will let me know?

150
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,660
你可是无所不知
I mean, you know all kinds of things.

151
00:08:33,660 --> 00:08:36,620
五音步抑扬格  伟大诗人的诗句
Iambic pentameter, the words of the great poets.

152
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:39,570
她这样签名是什么意思呢  "永远的  艾瑟尔"
What about the way she signed it? "Always, Ethel."

153
00:08:40,090 --> 00:08:41,330
你能想象到吗
Can you beat that?

154
00:08:41,330 --> 00:08:44,110
不只是"艾瑟尔"  而是"永远的  艾瑟尔"
Not just "Ethel." "Always, Ethel."

155
00:08:44,110 --> 00:08:46,800
汤米  如果我们能在日落前抵达某个城镇
Tommy, if we can find civilization by sundown,

156
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:50,010
我希望能爬出这铁皮车  一头钻进冰马蒂尼酒
I hope to climb out of this crate and into a cold martini.

157
00:08:50,010 --> 00:08:52,480
如果不是真心的  她就不会加上"永远的"
She's not the kind to use "always" if she didn't mean it.

158
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,530
如果她只想说自己是"艾瑟尔"
If she meant just "Ethel,"

159
00:08:53,530 --> 00:08:55,340
那她就不会加上"永远的"三个字
she'd write just "Ethel," not "always."

160
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:57,490
-你说呢  -看路  汤米
- Wouldn't you think? - The road, Tommy.

161
00:08:57,490 --> 00:08:58,530
我知道了
I know.

162
00:08:58,930 --> 00:09:01,800
你看一遍就懂我的意思了
You read it and see what I mean.

163
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:14,640
她爱我  不是吗
She loves me, don't you think?

164
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:37,600
曼克  我是奥森·威尔斯
Mank? It's Orson Welles.

165
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:42,980
-还能是谁  -我们该谈谈了
- Of course it is. - I think it's time we talked.

166
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:46,300
我洗耳恭听
I'm all ears.

167
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:53,330
{\an8}线圈式护眼笔记本

168
00:09:52,620 --> 00:09:55,710
曾是山上的一座城堡
Once a castle on a hill,

169
00:09:56,380 --> 00:09:59,350
如今已变成一段回忆
now a memory of what once was.

170
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:05,350
只身在他那尚未完工  却早已破败的享乐宫
Alone in his unfinished, already decaying pleasure palace,

171
00:10:05,350 --> 00:10:09,860
偏远冷淡  罕有人至  从未被拍成照片
aloof, seldom visited, never photographed,

172
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:15,470
我们看见一个老头穿着浴袍  抽着烟斗
we see an old man in a robe, smoking a pipe,

173
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:18,540
独自坐在泳池旁
sitting alone by his pool...

174
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:24,660
废弃的纸张散落在他的脚边
discarded pages scattered at his feet.

175
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:26,680
旁白
Narrator,

176
00:10:26,940 --> 00:10:33,810
"这位报业皇帝仍在执掌他的衰败王朝
"An emperor of newsprint continued to direct his failing empire,

177
00:10:33,810 --> 00:10:36,820
妄图像从前那样
vainly attempting to sway, as he once did,

178
00:10:36,820 --> 00:10:38,250
改变一个国度的命运
the destinies of a nation

179
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:40,900
而这个国度早已不再听命于他"
which had long since ceased to listen to him..."

180
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:43,970
不对  "不再信任他"
No. "Had ceased to trust him."

181
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:47,220
透过树梢  我们看见一位助手
We see through trees as an aide

182
