00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:55,950
总的来说有点混乱
All in all, it's a bit of a jumble.

518
00:30:55,950 --> 00:30:57,490
你说"混乱"还是"丛林"
Did you say "jumble" or "jungle"?

519
00:30:57,500 --> 00:30:59,200
各种话唠的情节大杂烩
A hodgepodge of talky episodes.

520
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:01,740
在时间线上跳来跳去的一堆碎片
A collection of fragments that leap around in time,

521
00:31:01,750 --> 00:31:03,290
像墨西哥跳豆一样
like Mexican jumping beans.

522
00:31:03,290 --> 00:31:04,910
欢迎来到我的脑内世界  老兄
Welcome to my mind, Old Sock.

523
00:31:04,910 --> 00:31:08,120
故事太散了  恐怕观众需要地图才能看懂
The story is so scattered, I'm afraid one will need a road map.

524
00:31:08,120 --> 00:31:09,750
你是说它一团糟
You mean it's a mess.

525
00:31:09,790 --> 00:31:11,290
你能不能简化一下
Would you consider simplifying?

526
00:31:11,290 --> 00:31:13,040
帕斯卡曾经说过
As Pascal once said,

527
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:14,910
"我要是时间更充裕
"If only I'd had more time,

528
00:31:14,910 --> 00:31:16,490
就会写一封更短的信"
I would have written a shorter letter."

529
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:19,200
我只想说  没人能那样写
All I am saying is no one can write like that.

530
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:23,080
但我就能  豪斯曼  我已经那样写了
But I can write like that, Houseman. I have.

531
00:31:23,080 --> 00:31:27,290
叙事就是一个大圆圈  像一个肉桂卷
The narrative is one big circle, like a cinnamon roll,

532
00:31:27,410 --> 00:31:30,830
而不是一条直指最近出口的直线
not a straight line pointing to the nearest exit.

533
00:31:30,830 --> 00:31:34,410
一个人的一生在两小时内是刻画不完的
You cannot capture a man's entire life in two hours.

534
00:31:34,410 --> 00:31:36,870
你只能寄希望于留个大概印象
All you can hope is to leave the impression of one.

535
00:31:36,870 --> 00:31:38,870
但没人想看莎士比亚式的作品
But nobody expects Shakespeare.

536
00:31:38,870 --> 00:31:42,620
观众花辛苦挣来的25分钱  不是为了看《麦克白》
People aren't spending their hard-earned 25 cents to see Macbeth.

537
00:31:42,620 --> 00:31:45,160
‎那个长着一张狗脸的大师就拍了《麦克白》
Maestro the Dog-Faced Boy did Macbeth.

538
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:48,330
{\an3}{\pos(380,235)}奥森·威尔斯拍了全黑人版的《麦克白》
将原本的苏格兰背景换成后革命时期的海地小岛
剧中增添巫毒祭祀中的唱跳击鼓

539
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:48,330
是"巫毒麦克白"  别被骗了  他就爱出风头
Voodoo Macbeth. Don't be fooled. He's a showman.

540
00:31:48,330 --> 00:31:50,830
一个耍把戏自我陶醉的街头艺人
Busker reveling in sleight of hand.

541
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:53,290
别自找麻烦  60天之内写完
Save yourself the trouble, be done in 60 days.

542
00:31:53,290 --> 00:31:55,870
他会看懂的  观众也会
He'll get this, and the audience will too.

543
00:31:55,870 --> 00:31:58,080
别担心了  吃点腌黄瓜
Stop worrying. Have a pickle.

544
00:31:58,080 --> 00:32:00,040
不了  谢谢  我不饿
No, thank you. I'm not hungry.

545
00:32:00,370 --> 00:32:02,160
自从我们到这儿我还没饿过
Haven't been since we got here.

546
00:32:03,750 --> 00:32:04,620
再见
Cheerio.

547
00:32:07,870 --> 00:32:11,290
埋头写  降低目标
Write hard. Aim low.

548
00:32:18,290 --> 00:32:19,870
上次说到哪里了  长官
Where were we, chief?

549
00:32:20,790 --> 00:32:22,000
你要怎么办
What are you gonna do?

550
00:32:22,790 --> 00:32:24,460
-什么怎么办  -他说得对
- About what? - He's right.

551
00:32:24,460 --> 00:32:25,830
你到圣诞节才能写完
You won't be done till Christmas.

552
00:32:25,830 --> 00:32:28,080
-什么  -你答应过的
- What? - You made a promise.

553
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:31,450
-我什么  -60天只剩下两周了
- I did what? - Sixty days is two weeks from now.

554
00:32:32,870 --> 00:32:34,580
上次说到哪里了
Where were we?

555
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:42,620
伯恩斯坦的独白  那个渡轮上的年轻女子
Bernstein's speech, the young woman on the ferry boat.

556
00:32:42,750 --> 00:32:45,120
麻烦读给我听
Read it back, please.

557
00:32:45,870 --> 00:32:50,000
"她身着白裙  撑着白阳伞
"A white dress she had on, and she was carrying a white parasol,

558
00:32:50,620 --> 00:32:55,250
我只看到她一眼  她根本没看到我
and I only saw her for one second, and she didn't see me at all."

559
00:32:56,120 --> 00:32:58,950
但那之后的一个月
"But I'll bet a month hasn't gone by since

560
00:32:58,950 --> 00:33:01,040
我无时无刻不想着那姑娘"
that I haven't thought of that girl."

561
00:33:02,870 --> 00:33:04,950
是曼凯维奇家族相册中的一幕吗
A snapshot from the Mankiewicz family album?

562
00:33:04,950 --> 00:33:06,330
算是吧
You might say that.

563
00:33:07,750 --> 00:33:09,660
真的很美...
It really is a gorgeous...

564
00:33:09,660 --> 00:33:11,500
在这里卡住很美
Spot to get stuck?

565
00:33:14,660 --> 00:33:16,990
伯恩斯坦的原型是路易·梅耶吗
Is Bernstein meant to be Louis Mayer?

566
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:18,620
如果形式服从功能的话
If form follows function.

567
00:33:18,620 --> 00:33:22,450
梅耶是条可悲的哈巴狗  奉承我们的查尔斯·福斯特吗
Mayer is the same pathetic sort of lap dog to our Charles Foster?

568
00:33:22,450 --> 00:33:25,080
伯恩斯坦这角色比他好多了
Bernstein is a far nicer character.

569
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:27,040
你不怎么喜欢梅耶
You don't much like Mayer.

570
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:29,660
我要是有朝一日上了电椅
If I ever go to the electric chair,

571
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:32,830
我很希望他坐在我腿上
I'd like him to be sitting in my lap.

572
00:33:35,790 --> 00:33:38,450
{\an7}{\pos(83.013,133.307)}外景  米高梅工作室  白天  1934年  闪回

573
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:41,080
每周750美元  只有你薪水的一半  赫尔曼
$750 a week? That's half what you make, Herman.

574
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:43,490
-你只是个初出茅庐的编剧  乔  -那又怎样
- You're a junior writer, Joe. - So?

575
00:33:43,500 --> 00:33:46,240
所以你的聪明才智只有你哥哥的一半
So, you're only half the wit your big brother is.

576
00:33:46,250 --> 00:33:50,040
-有多少笨蛋能挣到这么多  -赫尔  我看起来如何
- How many half-wits make that? - Herm, how do I look?

577
00:33:50,290 --> 00:33:54,330
-跟平时一样  很好  -今天我会面对什么流程
- You look like you. Fine. - What should I be expecting?

578
00:33:54,330 --> 00:33:58,040
你是我的亲戚  他已经把你当天才了
You're related to me. He already thinks you're a genius.

579
00:33:58,040 --> 00:33:59,540
-行了  -你好
- Enough. - Good day.

580
00:33:59,540 --> 00:34:02,330
如果你能做到以下两点  那么工作就是你的了
The job will be yours if you can do two things.

581
00:34:02,330 --> 00:34:06,540
一  别翻白眼  二  尽量别睡着
One, don't roll your eyes. Two, try not to fall asleep.

582
00:34:06,790 --> 00:34:08,410
这里又不是好莱坞的高尔峡谷
This isn't Gower Gulch.

583
00:34:08,410 --> 00:34:10,790
你想让我拍一部讲妓女的电影
You want I should make a picture about a prostitute?

584
00:34:10,790 --> 00:34:11,830
那有什么不好
What's wrong with that?

585
00:34:11,830 --> 00:34:13,660
我妈就是一个不折不扣的婊子
My mother was nothing but a whore.

586
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:16,620
你怎能那么说你自己的亲生母亲
You would talk about your own mother that way?

587
00:34:16,620 --> 00:34:18,910
那个给了你生命的女人
The woman who gave you life?

588
00:34:18,910 --> 00:34:22,330
你个忘恩负义的混蛋  我要割了你的卵蛋
You ungrateful bastard! I ought to cut your balls off!

589
00:34:22,330 --> 00:34:25,660
来啊  你个收废品的  我依然比你强
Do it, you fucking junk dealer! I'll still be the better man!

590
00:34:29,370 --> 00:34:31,950
LB  这位是我弟弟  乔
L.B., this is my brother, Joe.

591
00:34:31,950 --> 00:34:34,580
见到你很高兴  乔瑟夫  我是路易·梅耶
Nice to meet you, Joseph. I'm Louis Mayer.

592
00:34:34,580 --> 00:34:37,160
我都无法表达今天对他有多重要  路易
I can't tell you what this means to him, Louis.

593
00:34:37,160 --> 00:34:41,580
-他们都到了  梅耶先生  -这就去  乔  跟我走走
- They're all there, Mr. Mayer. - On my way. Joe, walk with me.

594
00:34:44,500 --> 00:34:47,500
{\an8}米高梅电影公司

595
00:34:47,500 --> 00:34:50,370
孩子  这家制片厂有三条工作守则
My boy, there are three work rules at this studio.

596
00:34:50,370 --> 00:34:54,080
第一条  为艺术而艺术
Rule number one. Ars gratia artis, art for art's sake.

597
00:34:54,080 --> 00:34:54,870
你好
How you doing?

598
00:34:54,870 --> 00:34:56,040
我们每年花在
One million dollars a year

599
00:34:56,040 --> 00:34:58,540
不会拍的剧本上的钱高达一百万美元
we spend on stories we never even film.

600
00:34:58,700 --> 00:35:02,330
为什么呢  我告诉你  它们没法让我哭
Why not? I'll tell you. They don't make me cry.

601
00:35:02,370 --> 00:35:04,870
什么能让我哭呢  情感
What makes me cry? Emotion.

602
00:35:04,870 --> 00:35:07,080
我哪里能感受到情感
Where do I feel emotion?

603
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:09,660
这里  这里还有这里
Here, here, and here.

604
00:35:09,660 --> 00:35:10,910
第二条
Rule number two.

605
00:35:10,910 --> 00:35:12,620
你可能听说过  米高梅的明星
You may have heard MGM has more stars

606
00:35:12,620 --> 00:35:14,080
比天上的星星还多
than there are in the heavens.

607
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:15,410
-别信  -梅耶先生
- Do not believe this. - Mr. Mayer.

608
00:35:15,410 --> 00:35:19,330
你好  我们只有一位明星  雄狮利奥
Hiya. We have only one star. That is Leo the Lion.

609
00:35:19,330 --> 00:35:20,660
千万别忘了
Never forget that.

610
00:35:20,660 --> 00:35:23,830
许多明星忘记了  所以他们现在在别处闪耀
Many stars have, and now they twinkle elsewhere.

611
00:35:23,830 --> 00:35:24,870
第三条
Rule number three.

612
00:35:24,870 --> 00:35:28,370
大家以为米高梅是米措-高文-梅耶的缩写
People think MGM stands for Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer.

613
00:35:28,370 --> 00:35:29,740
其实不是的
It does not.

614
00:35:29,750 --> 00:35:34,370
是梅耶大家庭的意思
It stands for Mayer's gantze mishpokhe, Mayer's whole family.

615
00:35:34,370 --> 00:35:35,700
千万别忘了
Never forget that.

616
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:38,000
有问题  找爸爸
You got a problem, come to Papa.

617
00:35:38,540 --> 00:35:40,160
我们这一行  买家出钱
This is a business where the buyer

618
00:35:40,160 --> 00:35:42,740
只能买到一段回忆
gets nothing for his money but a memory.

619
00:35:42,750 --> 00:35:45,540
他买下的东西依然属于卖家
What he bought still belongs to the man who sold it.

620
00:35:45,540 --> 00:35:47,120
这就是电影的真正魔力
That's the real magic of the movies,

621
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:49,330
其他人讲别的  你信都别信
and don't let anybody tell you different.

622
00:36:11,700 --> 00:36:14,700
我现在身陷困境
I find myself in a horrendous position,

623
00:36:14,700 --> 00:36:17,910
我只好跪求各位
and I come to all of you on bended knee.

624
00:36:19,500 --> 00:36:22,620
跟所有美国人一样  我们在受苦
We are suffering, as all Americans are,

625
00:36:22,620 --> 00:36:25,660
因为我国的经济不景气
from our country's terrible economic woes.

626
00:36:25,750 --> 00:36:29,450
普通老百姓没钱看电影
Good people, everyday people, can't afford to go to the movies.

627
00:36:29,450 --> 00:36:33,450
所以就连我们卓越的梦工厂
So even our preeminent dream factory...

628
00:36:34,290 --> 00:36:37,120
都面对着深重的财务困境
is in grave financial difficulty.

629
00:36:39,080 --> 00:36:42,700
我恳请米高梅大家庭的每一位
I am asking everyone in the MGM family

630
00:36:42,700 --> 00:36:44,910
迈出沉痛的一步
to take a painful step.

631
00:36:45,330 --> 00:36:48,540
我请求给各位减薪
I am asking to roll back salaries.

632
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:50,580
我也不想
I don't want to,

633
00:36:50,830 --> 00:36:55,830
但为了让这个神圣的地方继续存在  我不得不这样
but for this hallowed place to continue to exist, I am forced to.

634
00:36:56,200 --> 00:37:00,660
我不愿意因为钱这种事而拆散这个家
I won't break up this family over something like money.

635
00:37:01,500 --> 00:37:03,990
-要减薪多久  -应该不久
- How long are you asking for? - Shouldn't be long.

636
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:06,370
-要减多少  -一半
- How much are you asking for? - Half.

637
00:37:06,450 --> 00:37:07,700
-一半  -可能不到一半
- Half? - Could be less.

638
00:37:07,700 --> 00:37:10,290
所有人都减吗  你减吗  梅耶先生
Is everybody going to be pitching in? Are you, Mr. Mayer?

639
00:37:10,290 --> 00:37:14,080
真正的家人在顺境中相互扶持
Real families root for each other in the good times,

640
00:37:14,080 --> 00:37:17,580
在逆境中相互照应
take care of each other in tough ones.

641
00:37:17,950 --> 00:37:19,120
我们跟你一条心  LB
We're with you, L.B.

642
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:20,540
你也许是跟他一条心了  巴里摩尔
You may be, Mr. Barrymore,

643
00:37:20,540 --> 00:37:23,120
但是给器械工和电工减薪一半...
but a 50% pay cut for grips and electricians...

644
00:37:23,120 --> 00:37:26,620
八周  朋友们  就短短的八周
Eight weeks, my friends, eight short weeks.

645
00:37:26,620 --> 00:37:31,120
一旦罗斯福重开银行  就把钱都补给你们
As soon as FDR reopens the banks, you'll get back every penny.

646
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:35,000
这一点  LB·梅耶
On that, you have the sacred word

647
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:36,830
向你们郑重保证
of L.B. Mayer.

648
00:37:44,370 --> 00:37:46,290
我赞成
Well, I vote yes.

649
00:37:47,830 --> 00:37:50,830
-我也赞成  -我也是
- I do as well. - Me too.

650
00:38:10,290 --> 00:38:12,950
-我讲得怎么样  本  -很棒  梅耶先生
- How'd I do, Ben? - It was great, Mr. Mayer.

651
00:38:18,040 --> 00:38:21,660
这还算不上我见过的最可耻的事
Not even the most disgraceful thing I've ever seen.

652
00:38:27,870 --> 00:38:29,120
好
Good.

653
00:38:30,500 --> 00:38:31,650
好
Ok.

654
00:38:33,330 --> 00:38:35,040
-舒服吗  -舒服
- Yeah? - Oh, yeah.

655
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:37,450
行吗  好
Yeah? Okay.

656
00:38:37,540 --> 00:38:39,660
稍微往左一点儿
Maybe a little bit left?

657
00:38:39,660 --> 00:38:41,540
-行吗  -行
- Yeah? - Yeah.

658
00:38:41,540 --> 00:38:42,330
这里吗
Here?

659
00:38:42,750 --> 00:38:45,580
-对  -我得快点进城买打字机色带
- Yeah. - I've got to rush to town to get typewriter ribbon.

660
00:38:45,580 --> 00:38:48,200
-这是今早的剧本  -垃圾  全是垃圾
- Here are this morning's pages. - Dreck. It's all dreck!

661
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:50,240
别妄自菲薄  至少你又开始写了
Don't flagellate. At least you're writing again.

662
00:38:50,250 --> 00:38:53,200
没有一句能唱  一个音都唱不出来
None of it sings. None of it. Not a note.

663
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:54,750
你又不是在写歌剧
You're not writing an opera.

664
00:38:56,160 --> 00:38:57,160
喂
Hello?

665
00:38:59,160 --> 00:39:01,250
可我的确在写歌剧
But I am writing an opera.

666
00:39:03,910 --> 00:39:04,910
找你的
It's for you.

667
00:39:07,700 --> 00:39:09,740
-喂  -赫尔曼  我是乔
- Yeah? - Herman, it's Joe.

668
00:39:09,750 --> 00:39:11,790
你好啊  小伙子  有事吗
Hey, hey, kid. What's up?

669
00:39:11,790 --> 00:39:15,040
-问问你的情况  你适应得如何  -如履薄冰
- Checking in. How are you getting around? - Gingerly.

670
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:17,410
-休息过吗  -连日出都没见过
- Any rest? - Haven't seen a sunrise yet.

671
00:39:17,410 --> 00:39:19,540
你从来也没见过日出
You've never seen a sunrise.

672
00:39:19,540 --> 00:39:21,480
莎拉说你特意要了这个号码
Sara said you wanted this number.

673
00:39:21,480 --> 00:39:22,830
想听听你的声音
Just to hear your voice.

674
00:39:22,830 --> 00:39:26,790
她说你有工作上的事想和我谈谈
She said you had some work you wanted to talk about.

675
00:39:26,950 --> 00:39:30,410
我在想那个老剧本
I was thinking about that old play,

676
00:39:30,410 --> 00:39:31,700
《婆罗洲的野人》
The Wild Man of Borneo,

677
00:39:31,700 --> 00:39:32,830
你好久之前写的那个
the one you wrote in the Ice Age.

678
00:39:32,830 --> 00:39:36,370
人从不记得自己糟糕的作品  那个剧本太粗糙了
One never remembers one's disasters. It's considered gauche.

679
00:39:36,370 --> 00:39:37,790
